  "recommendations": [
    "NER recall is IDENTICAL at thr 0.30/0.50/0.70 (=0.90): spaCy emits a near-binary score (~0.85 base, 1.0 with a context-word boost), so any threshold in [0.30,0.85] gives the same NER recall. Balanced=0.70 vs compliant=0.50 does NOT change NER recall.",
    "NER recall first DROPS at thr=0.80 (0.85) — the un-boosted 0.85 spaCy spans get cut above 0.85. Keep the NER threshold at or below 0.80.",
    "At the balanced thr=0.70 the 0.40 structured FLOOR raises structured recall from 0.80 (no floor) to 0.97: without it, IP/URL (base 0.60) and bare DE_TAX_ID (base 0.50) would leak in balanced mode. The floor is JUSTIFIED and well-placed.",
    "Lowest structured raw score on corpus is 0.50 >= 0.40 floor: the floor admits every structured hit here without lowering precision (0 structured FP on clean docs across the sweep).",
    "0 STRUCTURED false positives on clean docs at EVERY threshold — the denylist + FP filter already strip structured noise, so the structured floor costs no precision.",
    "KNOWN-OPEN (residual spaCy NER FP on tech terms): 4 LOCATION FP on clean docs at thr=0.70 (e.g. 'Cisco-Hardware', 'Sophos-Firewalls', 'Security-Monitoring'). They score 0.85 — IDENTICAL to legit NER — so the FPs only clear at thr=0.90, where real NER recall collapses 0.90->0.21. Threshold tuning CANNOT fix this; the fix is denylist/context coverage (hyphenated tech compounds), not a higher threshold. Documented as known-open, not a regression."
  ],
